DOC:

Same par-file as background code. The entry "tstep" can be either 1 or 2,
and decides whether the background is downsampled in time by a factor of 2
or not. This is implemented since the pert-code might work with less modes than the bg-code.

the output for the pert-code is stored in a folder "bg_data" upon evaluation.
if the parameter "debug" is true, all the taylor coefficients from L and R are also stored
in folders, this is useful for reconstructing the whole background in Mathematica.
